The reason why I'm getting the compiler identification wrong is because the Unknown Compiler Message is set as:
{code:java}
"Unknown compiler: ${CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_VERSION} ${CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_VERSION}"
{code}
And I think it should be:
{code:java}
"Unknown compiler: ${CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_ID} ${CMAKE_CXX_COMPILER_VERSION}"
{code}
But the problem remains that it doesn't handle the Intel compiler (you can probably use -Wall like GNU, and the Intel compiler just ignores extra flags if it doesn't know what to do with then, so even if you get the exact ones a little wrong you should be fine).

